---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="AI Engineer specializing in multi-agent systems and agentic architectures. Based in Rome, Italy."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-12" transition:animate="fade">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl mb-4">About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none" transition:animate="fade">
      <p>
        I'm Matteo Antonini, an AI Engineer based in Rome, Italy.
      </p>
      <p>
        My background is unconventional: Economics undergrad, then a Master in Data Science
        and Machine Learning — both 110/110 cum laude at the University of Rome Tor Vergata.
        The degrees gave me the foundations. Most of what I actually know about AI I learned
        by building it.
      </p>

      <h2>What I do</h2>
      <p>
        I work as an AI Engineer. My focus is on agentic
        architectures: systems that don't just respond to prompts but reason across multiple
        steps, use tools, and coordinate several models to get things done.
      </p>
      <p>
        Clients are in energy, telco, and public administration. The hard problems aren't
        the models — they're everything that happens between a working demo and something
        that actually ships.
      </p>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Agentic AI</strong> — Google ADK, LangGraph, LangChain, Agno, MCP Server<br />
        <strong>LLMs</strong> — Azure OpenAI, Gemini, Claude, Deepseek<br />
        <strong>Cloud</strong> — GCP / Vertex AI, Azure, Cloud Run, Docker<br />
        <strong>Data</strong> — RAG pipelines, VectorDB, BigQuery, Snowflake, Airflow, dbt<br />
        <strong>Dev</strong> — Python, FastAPI, Dash, Streamlit<br />
        <strong>Automation</strong> — n8n, Apify
      </p>

      <h2>Teaching</h2>
      <p>
        I teach a module on multi-agent AI systems in the
        <a href="/teaching">Master CESMA program</a> at the University of Rome Tor Vergata.
        All course materials and code are open source and available on GitLab.
      </p>

      <h2>This blog</h2>
      <p>
        I write about what I build and what I learn. Multi-agent systems, agentic
        architectures, tooling, patterns that work, and patterns that don't.
        No tutorials for their own sake — only things I've actually used.
      </p>

      <hr />

